1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,380 --> 00:01:42,270
[I Don't Want To Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:49,539
[Episode 2: The day
I get to call the shots]

4
00:01:51,229 --> 00:01:52,880
Who are you?  Let me go.

5
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,759
Li Qing Tong?

6
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,540
Who are you?

7
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:04,700
Your father is Li Wu Si.

8
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,760
Your mother is

9
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:07,880
Liu Feng Xia.

10
00:02:09,850 --> 00:02:10,850
How did you know that?

11
00:02:11,850 --> 00:02:13,400
You really are Li Qing Tong!

12
00:02:13,620 --> 00:02:15,140
Who on earth are you?

13
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:17,340
How did you know the names of my parents?

14
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:18,650
What are you doing?

15
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:20,020
I'll clap you!

16
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:22,040
Why did you knock me down?

17
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:23,470
Qing Tong.

18
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,440
Qing Tong.

19
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:28,770
I was deterring her.

20
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:31,140
Auntie.

21
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:34,230
Am I really her daughter?

22
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,329
Am I really related to her?

23
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:37,900
Who is she?

24
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,640
Is she in cahoots with the driver?

25
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,760
Fan Shui Shui?

26
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,300
Fan Shui Shui.

27
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,560
What are you doing?

28
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:48,620
You can talk

29
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:49,550
but keep your hands off.

30
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,360
Listen!

31
00:02:50,450 --> 00:02:52,560
You are no match for me.

32
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:55,700
You've been fat since you were young?

33
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:57,160
What?

34
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,310
Wait a minute.

35
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:02,970
She seems to know us.

36
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,220
She even knows the names of my parents.

37
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:07,370
[What should I do?]

38
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:09,520
[I can't say that I'm her daughter.]

39
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,460
Is she a human trafficker?

40
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:14,800
Let's get out of here!

41
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,180
Li Qing Tong!

42
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,760
I wanted to see if you were loyal.

43
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:21,400
So you've really forgotten me.

44
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:23,280
What are you talking about?

45
00:03:23,380 --> 00:03:26,220
[When I was a child,
I had a good friend called Hua.]

46
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,370
[We used to dance together.]

47
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:28,470
[It was especially nice.]

48
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,740
[Unfortunately, she transferred
to Shenzhen.]

49
00:03:30,829 --> 00:03:31,930
We used to dance together.

50
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:33,340
Don't you remember?

51
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:39,540
We danced by the river.

52
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,170
You even lost your hat when we danced.

53
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:42,400
Remember?

54
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,100
Hua?

55
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,320
Conscientious for you.

56
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:00,000
Hua!

57
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:03,040
Hua, it's really you!

58
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:05,240
It's you, Hua!

59
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:07,310
Fan Shui Shui, look, it's Hua!

60
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,410
Hua.

61
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:09,520
Hua?

62
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,780
-The one who went to Shenzhen?
-Yeah.

63
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:13,050
Hua, you're back.

64
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:14,090
You're back!

65
00:04:14,210 --> 00:04:15,110
You're back!

66
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,790
You're back, Hua.

67
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:19,010
[She has been a fool since young.]

68
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,959
[She believes in everything.]

69
00:04:22,019 --> 00:04:24,360
Can you stop hopping when you walk?

70
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,340
Tell us.

71
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,330
Why did you come back?

72
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:27,580
What is Shenzhen like?

73
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,450
You've been abroad.

74
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,670
What is it like abroad?

75
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:30,620
Please ask one by one.

76
00:04:30,710 --> 00:04:32,530
How can I answer so many questions?

77
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,080
Why have you grown so tall?

78
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:35,250
Why are you so tall?

79
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:36,880
Stop jumping.

80
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:43,130
Come in.

81
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:44,840
Mum.

82
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:46,420
Look who's here?

83
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,720
Who?

84
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:48,560
It's Hua.

85
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:49,960
She's Hua.

86
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:52,020
[So this is my grandma?]

87
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:54,290
[She is different from what I remember.]

88
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,920
[She's pretty.]

89
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:56,850
My God.

90
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,150
Hua?

91
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:00,750
I can hardly recognize you.

92
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:01,570
Take off your coat.

93
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:02,670
Come in and warm yourself up.

94
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,000
I'll get you some food.

95
00:05:08,690 --> 00:05:09,570
Come on.

96
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:15,990
Come, quick.

97
00:05:16,130 --> 00:05:17,180
Have a seat.

98
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:27,190
Why do you look different?

99
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:29,210
How different?

100
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,360
You're different in every way.

101
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,350
She's prettier than ever.

102
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:36,400
I remember that

103
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:38,600
you had single eyelids.

104
00:05:38,690 --> 00:05:39,750
Look at you now.

105
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,170
You have big, double-lidded eyes.

106
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,340
How nice you look!

107
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:44,140
Now you have short hair.

108
00:05:44,670 --> 00:05:45,360
Hua.

109
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:47,570
When you were a child,
your mum cut your bangs

110
00:05:47,659 --> 00:05:48,570
and you cried for a week.

111
00:05:48,659 --> 00:05:49,780
Do you remember?

112
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,090
You're really different now.

113
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:53,360
You're a beautiful young lady now.

114
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:55,340
Everyone will change after growing up.

115
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,540
Right? Grand...

116
00:05:57,659 --> 00:05:58,680
Grand...

117
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,320
It's not nice to have the same haircut

118
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:01,510
all the time.

119
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,220
Right, auntie?

120
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:03,730
Yes. You look better now.

121
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:04,790
More fashionable than before.

122
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,440
Look at Qing Tong.

123
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,660
So dowdy.

124
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:08,540
The older, the uglier.

125
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:09,760
Who's uglier?

126
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:10,760
You, of course.

127
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:13,980
Come on, Hua.

128
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:15,340
Eat it.

129
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:17,750
What's this?

130
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:18,980
Frozen pear.

131
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,960
It used to be your favourite.

132
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:22,120
Look at her.

133
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:23,320
She even forgot the frozen pear

134
00:06:23,410 --> 00:06:24,710
after living in the south for a long time.

135
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:26,920
It's been too long.

136
00:06:27,010 --> 00:06:27,890
I forgot it.

137
00:06:28,010 --> 00:06:28,990
Eat up.

138
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,170
The teeth hurts.

139
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:36,170
Okay, you wait here.

140
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:37,600
I'll cook for you.

141
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:39,850
Stop eating.

142
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:41,120
Let's check out my bedroom.

143
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:42,090
Let's go.

144
00:06:46,470 --> 00:06:47,570
It's my bedroom.

145
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:11,340
[Writing book]

146
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,300
You get your own room?

147
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,520
I shared with my grandma
when I was a child.

148
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:25,210
Now I have the room to myself
after she went back to the countryside.

149
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:27,130
I'm 17 years old.

150
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:29,040
Finally I have my own bedroom.

151
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,420
You have it, but I don't.

152
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,230
What?

153
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,350
I don't have my own bedroom.

154
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:35,390
Where do you sleep without a bedroom?

155
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,730
A shabby apartment.

156
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:38,790
I sleep in the living room.

157
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,930
My mum gets the bedroom.

158
00:07:40,170 --> 00:07:41,340
How about your father?

159
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,409
[I should ask you the same question.]

160
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:46,740
I don't know where he has gone.

161
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:49,340
So you came back

162
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,890
to look for your father this time?

163
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,060
No.

164
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,580
I came back for you.

165
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,290
Really?

166
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,440
Hua, that's very kind of you.

167
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,750
I knew you didn't forget me.

168
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:03,170
We were so close before.

169
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:05,730
I cried for days after your left.

170
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:08,900
Then I'll stay with you for a few more days.

171
00:08:09,010 --> 00:08:10,300
How many days can you stay here?

172
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,090
I don't know.

173
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:16,600
Then just live in my house.

174
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:17,770
My bedroom is so big.

175
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:19,160
We can sleep together.

176
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,000
Will that be okay?

177
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:21,950
Why not?

178
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,630
I'm going to tell my mum.

179
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:25,010
Mum!

180
00:08:29,850 --> 00:08:31,380
The dumplings are so big.

181
00:08:32,549 --> 00:08:34,210
We don't have small dumplings here.

182
00:08:35,210 --> 00:08:36,260
Try it.

183
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,299
Eat directly?

184
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,330
Here's vinegar.

185
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,490
Eat with a clove of garlic.

186
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:44,680
-A clove of garlic.
-I don't eat shallot, ginger or garlic.

187
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:48,240
I didn't know that.

188
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:50,090
Let me cook something else for you.

189
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:51,050
It's fine, auntie.

190
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,390
I can eat directly.

191
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,240
I'm back.

192
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:58,620
Happy Meal!

193
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:02,820
Want a bite?

194
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:04,320
Give it to me!

195
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,260
How old is your daughter?

196
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:07,780
She still eats Happy Meal?

197
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:08,900
No matter how old she is,

198
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:11,000
she's always my little daughter.

199
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:12,980
Can't she have Happy Meal
for the festival?

200
00:09:13,070 --> 00:09:14,250
What festival?

201
00:09:17,570 --> 00:09:20,200
[This is my grandpa
whom I have never met,]

202
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,630
[Li Wu Si.]

203
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,570
[Li Qing Tong said]

204
00:09:24,810 --> 00:09:27,450
[he was the most handsome man
in the world.]

205
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,590
[Well...]

206
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:31,550
[He's just so so.]

207
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:35,880
We have a guest.
Aren't you going to introduce her?

208
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:36,770
Hello, uncle.

209
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,840
Hello, hello.

210
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,300
She's Hua.

211
00:09:39,940 --> 00:09:41,140
My childhood friend.

212
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,110
Do you remember?

213
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,670
How can he remember?

214
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,450
He even forgot us.

215
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:53,400
I've got it.

216
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,930
The girl that went to Russia.

217
00:09:57,090 --> 00:09:58,560
Russia?

218
00:09:58,710 --> 00:09:59,730
Shenzhen.

219
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:00,820
Oh, it's Shenzhen.

220
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,040
I got it wrong.

221
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:03,910
I've got it now.

222
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:06,020
You went with your parents.

223
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:06,990
Right?

224
00:10:08,770 --> 00:10:09,790
Right?

225
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,690
How are your parents in Shenzhen?

226
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:13,170
I haven't seen them in ages.

227
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,340
They're fine.

228
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,600
Li Wu Si.

229
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:18,100
You had a drink, right?

230
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,120
No.

231
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,500
No?

232
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:26,740
I can smell the alcohol
from a distance.

233
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:28,880
It's their fault.

234
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,770
Blame them.
They poured the drink into my glass.

235
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:31,890
I said I wouldn't drink.

236
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:32,850
But they poured anyway.

237
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:34,290
I had to drink it now that they poured.

238
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:35,640
Stop lying to me.

239
00:10:35,890 --> 00:10:36,790
How much did you drink?

240
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,010
Three shots.

241
00:10:44,940 --> 00:10:46,430
Just three?

242
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:50,320
It's true.

243
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,620
Really?

244
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:58,250
Three, plus three more.

245
00:10:58,340 --> 00:10:59,460
And another three.

246
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:00,540
Better to round it up, right?

247
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:01,490
Round it up?

248
00:11:01,580 --> 00:11:02,750
Round it up, you say?

249
00:11:02,830 --> 00:11:03,870
Liu Feng Xia!

250
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,250
How dare you!

251
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:11,960
Don't worry.

252
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:16,240
Help yourself.

253
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:18,440
You'll get it at night.

254
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,180
Li Wu Si.

255
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:24,330
Do you remember what the doctor said?

256
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:25,300
Of course.

257
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,570
If you are paralysed in the future,

258
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:27,520
just have your daughter take care of you.

259
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:29,050
I don't care.

260
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,020
Hua is here for the first time.

261
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,520
Don't frighten her.

262
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:36,350
Hua, eat dumplings.

263
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,740
Hua.

264
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:38,500
Never mind.

265
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,840
This is how our family is.

266
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,750
Auntie

267
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,720
is not good

268
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:42,820
at talking.

269
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:43,940
But she's good at making dumplings.

270
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:44,850
Guinness Big Dumpling.

271
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:46,040
Very delicious.

272
00:11:46,130 --> 00:11:47,180
Let me have a bite.

273
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:48,530
Wash your hands.

274
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:53,920
Hurry up.

275
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:55,560
Wash my hands.

276
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,560
Why does he always like showing off?

277
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,490
[Peony Hotel]

278
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,880
Hello?

279
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:15,610
[Hello.]

280
00:12:15,740 --> 00:12:16,920
[I'm Li Jin Bu.]

281
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:21,880
Why haven't you come back yet?

282
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:23,850
Did you go to find Li Qing Tong today?

283
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,880
I know she asked for leave
and didn't come to school.

284
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:27,490
I've found her.

285
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:28,920
I'm in her house now.

286
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:31,180
Then when will you come back?

287
00:12:31,270 --> 00:12:32,270
I'll pick you up.

288
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,700
I'm not going back.

289
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:35,020
I'm going to stay here.

290
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:37,890
[Please tell Mrs Peony]

291
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:39,320
[I'll go back to visit her tomorrow.]

292
00:12:40,810 --> 00:12:41,690
Okay.

293
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,390
[Hua, would you like to drink soda?]

294
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,180
That's all. Bye.

295
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,080
Bye.

296
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,530
I want to watch My Fair Princess..

297
00:12:58,740 --> 00:12:59,740
My Fair Princess?

298
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:01,520
Legend of Dagger Lee
will begin in a minute.

299
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,150
Go do your homework.

300
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,390
Why do you bother
fighting over the TV?

301
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:12,150
Have you ever won?

302
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,680
Here, Hua.

303
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:14,740
Have a soft drink.

304
00:13:15,380 --> 00:13:17,030
-Thank you.
-Hua, don't drink too much.

305
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,000
It's not good for you.

306
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,300
You drink less too.

307
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:20,810
Hua is our guest.

308
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,000
Just let her drink.

309
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,640
Keep spoiling them.

310
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,540
Hua.

311
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,250
What's your real name?

312
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,640
Li Jin Bu.

313
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,340
Aren't you Yang Fang Hua?

314
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:33,830
Why are you called Li Jin Bu?

315
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:35,170
I have changed my name.

316
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,800
Even your last name?

317
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:43,370
My parents divorced.

318
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:44,880
I took my mum's surname.

319
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:48,070
Divorced?

320
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:49,930
Why?

321
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,940
Didn't they go to Shenzhen
to start a business?

322
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:53,670
Why did they get divorced?

323
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:55,450
Li.

324
00:13:55,620 --> 00:13:57,660
Her parents are a model couple, right?

325
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,480
Yes, I remember that.

326
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,320
Right?

327
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:00,390
Look.

328
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,000
Your father

329
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,390
cheated on your mother?

330
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,580
My dad...

331
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:09,600
My dad...

332
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,160
My dad...

333
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:13,720
My mum is the problematic one.

334
00:14:14,650 --> 00:14:16,070
What's wrong with your mother?

335
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,630
My mum is unreliable
has no sense of responsibility.

336
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:19,620
She only quarrels with me every day.

337
00:14:19,710 --> 00:14:20,500
She doesn't care about me at all.

338
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:22,160
We butt heads all the time.

339
00:14:23,290 --> 00:14:24,240
Anyway, there is something wrong

340
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:25,220
with my mum.

341
00:14:26,070 --> 00:14:28,220
How can your mother do that?

342
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:29,940
She is too irresponsible.

343
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:30,900
Right.

344
00:14:32,180 --> 00:14:33,880
You're still kids.

345
00:14:33,970 --> 00:14:34,850
Childish.

346
00:14:36,110 --> 00:14:37,580
You've never been parents.

347
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:39,330
You have no idea how hard it is

348
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,640
to be a parent.

349
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:42,190
That's right.

350
00:14:42,630 --> 00:14:44,420
I think I won't be like her mother

351
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:45,910
when I become a parent.

352
00:14:47,010 --> 00:14:47,800
Isn't it too early

353
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:49,390
to think about this?

354
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:51,920
Hua.

355
00:14:52,450 --> 00:14:54,190
Does your mother know you have come back?

356
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,340
Yes.

357
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,680
That's fine.

358
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:58,280
Don't worry.

359
00:14:58,370 --> 00:14:59,990
Just stay at our house.

360
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,920
I'll talk with your mother
when I meet her.

361
00:15:02,010 --> 00:15:03,000
I'll tell her to treat you better.

362
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:04,080
My goodness.

363
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:05,670
You even want to talk to Hua's mother?

364
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:08,260
Don't meddle in such matters.

365
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:11,090
Hua.

366
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:13,030
Don't go back to the hotel.

367
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,620
Just stay here.

368
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:16,080
I'll talk with your mother

369
00:15:16,170 --> 00:15:17,310
when I meet her later.

370
00:15:17,540 --> 00:15:19,340
I'm good at

371
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:20,750
educating a child.

372
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:25,210
She's right.

373
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:27,640
She does well in ideological work.

374
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:29,480
She can definitely persuade your mother.

375
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:30,460
Don't worry.

376
00:15:33,570 --> 00:15:34,620
Yu Fen.

377
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,200
What are you doing?

378
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:37,500
Have you eaten yet?

379
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:42,070
Do you know the Yang
that worked at the car factory?

380
00:15:43,130 --> 00:15:44,560
His family moved to Shenzhen.

381
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,500
You know, the devoted couple.

382
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:50,050
They divorced.

383
00:15:50,810 --> 00:15:51,840
So I'm telling you.

384
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:52,810
Don't allow your husband

385
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:54,200
to work elsewhere.

386
00:15:54,290 --> 00:15:56,210
Otherwise, you need to be careful.

387
00:15:56,290 --> 00:15:57,470
What if something happened?

388
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,490
What are you doing?

389
00:15:58,580 --> 00:15:59,320
What are you doing?

390
00:15:59,410 --> 00:16:00,410
I haven't finished my call.

391
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,370
Why are you gossiping
when Hua is right here?

392
00:16:02,450 --> 00:16:03,370
Gossip?

393
00:16:03,450 --> 00:16:05,590
It's what she said.

394
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,500
I have to warn Yu Fen.

395
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,470
What if Wang cheated on her?

396
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:10,410
-Come here. Let's talk.
-What?

397
00:16:10,490 --> 00:16:11,290
-To discuss something.
-What?

398
00:16:11,370 --> 00:16:12,930
Legend of Dagger Lee will begin in a minute.

399
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:13,560
Just a few minutes.

400
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:15,390
Come on. Let's talk.

401
00:16:25,590 --> 00:16:26,520
Hua.

402
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:29,140
I didn't know you're suffering.

403
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:31,790
Don't worry.

404
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,070
I will take good care
of you in the future.

405
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,850
Watch TV.

406
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:40,830
[I never thought that one day]

407
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,870
[I would see 17-year-old
Li Qing Tong this way.]

408
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:45,730
[And my grandparents]

409
00:16:45,810 --> 00:16:48,190
[whom I only knew about
in my distant memory.]

410
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:51,180
[They are alive and kicking
in front of me.]

411
00:16:52,490 --> 00:16:53,680
[If]

412
00:16:53,770 --> 00:16:55,230
[this is a dream,]

413
00:16:55,570 --> 00:16:57,350
[I want to take my time waking up.]

414
00:16:58,500 --> 00:16:59,760
[Because]

415
00:16:59,940 --> 00:17:01,440
[it's enviable]

416
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:02,900
[to have a warm family.]

417
00:17:04,619 --> 00:17:07,849
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

418
00:17:07,849 --> 00:17:10,160
[Year 2 Class 3]

419
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:18,819
[Monthly Maths Exam]

420
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,339
[Monthly Maths Exam]

421
00:17:22,730 --> 00:17:24,470
Why is your score so high?

422
00:17:27,890 --> 00:17:29,040
You are the only one who can say

423
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:31,630
such irresponsible words in this world.

424
00:17:32,410 --> 00:17:33,610
You got more than ten points last time.

425
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,430
This time you got around 30 points.

426
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:36,920
Whose did you copy?

427
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:37,770
Shut up.

428
00:17:37,850 --> 00:17:39,620
Just pretend you didn't see
and throw away the paper.

429
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:42,080
Pretend I never took it.

430
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:44,720
No, thanks.

431
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,490
So Hua is living with you?

432
00:17:52,550 --> 00:17:54,420
Why is she back now?

433
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:55,530
It's not holiday season.

434
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:56,990
Is she not going to school?

435
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,470
She said her parents got divorced.

436
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:01,060
She is going to study abroad.

437
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,480
But that's a matter for the adults
to deal with.

438
00:18:02,570 --> 00:18:03,410
This time

439
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,230
she came back to see me.

440
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:11,110
Is it delicious?

441
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:17,520
What are you doing?

442
00:18:20,590 --> 00:18:21,650
Well,

443
00:18:21,970 --> 00:18:24,180
a girl called Li Jin Bu

444
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:25,910
is living in your house, right?

445
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,040
How did you know that?

446
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,300
Do you know her?

447
00:18:31,330 --> 00:18:32,240
Of course.

448
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,010
She lost her luggage.

449
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:35,250
She had no money.

450
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:37,350
My mum took her in for two days.

451
00:18:39,370 --> 00:18:41,390
So she stayed in your hotel.

452
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:43,290
Mrs Peony is nice.

453
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:45,070
I'll thank her next time.

454
00:18:48,140 --> 00:18:49,660
Will she continue to live with you?

455
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:50,420
Yes.

456
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:52,070
Is your house big enough?

457
00:18:52,330 --> 00:18:53,850
Of course.

458
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:54,760
We sleep on the same bed.

459
00:18:54,850 --> 00:18:56,070
It's very spacious.

460
00:18:59,340 --> 00:19:00,920
What's your plan for New Year's Eve?

461
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:02,710
What?

462
00:19:03,450 --> 00:19:05,000
Would you like to join us
on New Year's Eve?

463
00:19:05,090 --> 00:19:06,920
I've figured out what gift to give you.

464
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:08,920
Is it necessary to give
a gift for New Year's Eve?

465
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,380
Why not?

466
00:19:12,150 --> 00:19:13,370
What's the gift?

467
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:14,800
It's a millennium
and the bridge of two centuries.

468
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:16,440
Only once in a lifetime.

469
00:19:21,890 --> 00:19:23,510
Yes, I have to prepare a gift.

470
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:30,570
Did you hear that?
Duan Xiao will give me a gift.

471
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:31,650
Excited?

472
00:19:31,730 --> 00:19:33,000
Why should I be excited?

473
00:19:33,090 --> 00:19:34,590
He won't give me a gift.

474
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:44,640
Xiao.

475
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,600
Xiao.

476
00:19:46,020 --> 00:19:46,770
Will you go with us on New Year's Eve?

477
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:48,110
I have an appointment with them.

478
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:48,990
No.

479
00:19:49,110 --> 00:19:49,810
Come on.

480
00:19:49,890 --> 00:19:51,910
Many girls are waiting to spend
New Year's Eve with you.

481
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:52,930
Whatever.

482
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:56,370
Think about it.

483
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:05,390
Have you taken the medicine?

484
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:06,490
Yes.

485
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:09,020
You have to get better soon.

486
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:09,830
What if

487
00:20:09,910 --> 00:20:11,630
you can't join us on New Year's Eve?

488
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:12,890
New Year's Eve?

489
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,040
Yes.

490
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:15,450
We have an outing on that day.

491
00:20:15,530 --> 00:20:16,990
You must come along.

492
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:19,360
I'm not going.

493
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:20,460
Why?

494
00:20:21,090 --> 00:20:22,540
I don't know your friends.

495
00:20:22,630 --> 00:20:24,080
How embarrassing will it be
if I go with you.

496
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,080
No worries.

497
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:28,240
You'll know them when you come.

498
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:30,230
We are all very easy to get along with.

499
00:20:33,790 --> 00:20:35,630
Come, come.

500
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:37,960
I don't want to go if you don't come.

501
00:20:38,060 --> 00:20:39,960
It is the new millennium.

502
00:20:40,130 --> 00:20:42,310
Once in the lifetime.

503
00:20:43,690 --> 00:20:44,750
I know.

504
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,260
You need to drink more water.

505
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,870
It's snowing heavily here.

506
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,900
It's like this every year.

507
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:16,820
Li Qing Tong.

508
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:17,990
Going home?

509
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:20,670
Be careful on the way.

510
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:30,830
Why does he suddenly care about me?

511
00:21:32,330 --> 00:21:34,450
Maybe he's in fact caring about me.

512
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:35,770
Of course not.

513
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,460
He must care about me.

514
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,570
Mum, I'm back.

515
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:43,850
Where is Hua? Hua.

516
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:45,720
Stop shouting.

517
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,180
She just fell asleep.

518
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,550
Why so early?

519
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,870
She had a fever.

520
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,430
So she just went to bed
after taking medicine.

521
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:54,630
Stop shouting.

522
00:21:56,710 --> 00:21:57,640
Who is it?

523
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,140
Hello, auntie.

524
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,830
I'm Li Qing Tong's classmate.

525
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:13,540
Here.

526
00:22:13,650 --> 00:22:14,530
Drink some water.

527
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:15,720
Thank you.

528
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:17,400
Have you eaten?

529
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:18,280
Not yet.

530
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:19,320
Then have a meal here.

531
00:22:19,410 --> 00:22:20,710
I'll cook for you.

532
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:22,680
Okay. Then I'll have a meal here.

533
00:22:22,770 --> 00:22:23,670
Sure.

534
00:22:26,290 --> 00:22:27,640
What are you doing here?

535
00:22:27,730 --> 00:22:28,610
I came to see you.

536
00:22:29,540 --> 00:22:30,760
But what are you looking for?

537
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:32,370
Nothing.

538
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,260
Why did you come to see me?

539
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:38,360
What's up?

540
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:41,270
I can't solve a few math problems.

541
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,350
I want to ask you.

542
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:51,880
You got 85 points in math.
I got 20.

543
00:22:51,970 --> 00:22:53,430
You're asking me?

544
00:22:54,290 --> 00:22:55,350
I...

545
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,120
Maybe you can do it?

546
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,990
Never in a million years!

547
00:23:04,630 --> 00:23:06,180
Then tell me which problem
you can't solve.

548
00:23:06,270 --> 00:23:07,250
I'll teach you.

549
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,610
What's wrong with you?

550
00:23:19,050 --> 00:23:20,160
I'm finally out of school.

551
00:23:20,250 --> 00:23:21,290
I don't want to look at homework.

552
00:23:21,370 --> 00:23:22,480
You can find someone else
if you want to study.

553
00:23:22,570 --> 00:23:23,450
Go away.

554
00:23:23,540 --> 00:23:24,420
I'm watching TV.

555
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:29,850
This one.

556
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:31,000
This is my favourite.

557
00:23:31,090 --> 00:23:32,040
It's called...

558
00:23:32,130 --> 00:23:33,040
What is its name again?

559
00:23:33,140 --> 00:23:34,070
I forgot.

560
00:23:34,190 --> 00:23:35,450
But I'll go after finishing this episode.

561
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:36,330
Auntie is cooking for me.

562
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:37,440
I have to eat.

563
00:23:37,540 --> 00:23:38,330
Don't worry about me.

564
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:39,980
I'll watch it alone.

565
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:47,050
Have you had enough?

566
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:48,080
Yes.

567
00:23:48,170 --> 00:23:49,320
Okay. I'll clear it away.

568
00:23:49,410 --> 00:23:50,720
-I'll help you.
-No.

569
00:23:50,810 --> 00:23:51,690
Just sit here.

570
00:23:57,420 --> 00:23:59,060
You have watched TV

571
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,250
and had a meal.

572
00:24:00,330 --> 00:24:02,190
Why not go home?

573
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,850
Aren't they airing the next episode?

574
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:10,770
Even the TV stations are off duty.

575
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,820
Okay then.

576
00:24:14,910 --> 00:24:16,510
I'll leave now.

577
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,260
In fact,

578
00:24:27,390 --> 00:24:28,700
I came to ask...

579
00:24:28,790 --> 00:24:30,690
Hua, why are you up?

580
00:24:32,940 --> 00:24:34,840
I almost forgot you were here.

581
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,480
Why are you here?

582
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:38,330
Since I met you by chance,

583
00:24:38,410 --> 00:24:39,570
I'm not in a hurry to go back.

584
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:40,780
Let's have a chat.

585
00:24:40,870 --> 00:24:42,060
You want to drink water?

586
00:24:42,190 --> 00:24:43,070
I'll pour it for you.

587
00:25:03,490 --> 00:25:04,600
The bed is so small.

588
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:06,190
Is it enough for you two?

589
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:09,240
What do you really want?

590
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:23,400
Can you go out for a while?

591
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:24,880
-I want to talk to her.
-Hua.

592
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:25,850
I...

593
00:25:26,210 --> 00:25:27,170
I'll leave after a few words.

594
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:28,310
Don't come in.

595
00:25:37,660 --> 00:25:38,600
What are you doing?

596
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:41,920
I came to apologize to you today.

597
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:43,880
For what?

598
00:25:43,970 --> 00:25:45,630
I said you were a psychopath,

599
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:46,830
a gangster

600
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:47,860
and a thief.

601
00:25:48,010 --> 00:25:49,870
And I fought with you in the hotel.

602
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:51,750
That's all my fault.

603
00:25:52,330 --> 00:25:53,630
I shouldn't have done that.

604
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:55,380
I shouldn't have called you that.

605
00:25:56,220 --> 00:25:58,040
I hope we can make up.

606
00:25:58,650 --> 00:26:01,040
We agreed to bury the hatchet, right?

607
00:26:01,130 --> 00:26:02,920
And I'm not angry with you.

608
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:04,300
That's informal.

609
00:26:04,390 --> 00:26:05,620
In order to apologize to you

610
00:26:06,290 --> 00:26:07,710
I bought you a gift.

611
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:09,540
The New Year's Eve is coming.

612
00:26:09,670 --> 00:26:11,210
You can regard it as a New Year gift.

613
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,540
What's this?

614
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:17,030
I know you're afraid of the cold.

615
00:26:17,150 --> 00:26:19,010
So I chose a thick scarf.

616
00:26:19,090 --> 00:26:19,970
It's very warm.

617
00:26:20,130 --> 00:26:21,670
Open it and try it on.

618
00:26:28,950 --> 00:26:30,140
Did you buy it yourself?

619
00:26:30,230 --> 00:26:30,990
Yes.

620
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:32,690
I went to the best store in Tieyuan

621
00:26:32,780 --> 00:26:34,560
to choose one.

622
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,200
You have to take it.

623
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:37,400
Or else

624
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,320
it means you don't accept my apology.

625
00:26:40,630 --> 00:26:42,170
I'll accept it

626
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:43,560
since you said so.

627
00:26:43,890 --> 00:26:45,940
So you have forgiven me, right?

628
00:26:49,630 --> 00:26:51,000
Let's shake hands and make up.

629
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:08,760
Done.

630
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:15,320
Hua, you...

631
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:17,940
I'll... I'll go now.

632
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:21,440
Bye, Li Qing Tong.

633
00:27:26,100 --> 00:27:27,370
What were you doing just now?

634
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:29,880
There was a misunderstanding.

635
00:27:29,970 --> 00:27:31,630
We shook hands and made up today.

636
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:39,010
What's this?

637
00:27:39,450 --> 00:27:41,620
He said it's a New Year's gift for me?

638
00:27:44,210 --> 00:27:45,510
New Year's gift.

639
00:28:04,890 --> 00:28:06,790
-It looks nice.
-Does the colour suit me?

640
00:28:07,010 --> 00:28:07,990
It's nice.

641
00:28:08,610 --> 00:28:09,490
It looks nice, right?

642
00:28:23,650 --> 00:28:24,750
Stop putting it on.

643
00:28:30,650 --> 00:28:31,890
We held hands.

644
00:28:31,980 --> 00:28:32,960
What?

645
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:39,400
What?

646
00:28:39,630 --> 00:28:41,560
How can you hold hands with a thief?

647
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:43,750
Don't talk nonsense.

648
00:28:43,860 --> 00:28:45,090
She's a good girl.

649
00:28:45,250 --> 00:28:46,540
How can she be a thief?

650
00:28:46,930 --> 00:28:48,360
You said that yourself.

651
00:28:48,450 --> 00:28:50,150
You said she stole your bicycle.

652
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:53,120
She held my hand first.

653
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:55,430
My God.

654
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,210
What a terrible girl.

655
00:28:59,370 --> 00:29:01,190
Why is she a terrible girl?

656
00:29:01,470 --> 00:29:03,310
Shaking hands and making up
is a formality.

657
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,890
You know nothing.

658
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:22,840
I'm telling you.

659
00:29:22,930 --> 00:29:24,650
Although it's artificial,

660
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:27,860
it's more colourful than any other types.

661
00:29:28,420 --> 00:29:29,370
Yeah.

662
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:30,180
Tong.

663
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:31,580
There's a problem with you.

664
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:32,990
Your eye shadow is still too light.

665
00:29:33,070 --> 00:29:34,060
It should be like mine,

666
00:29:34,150 --> 00:29:35,350
bling bling.

667
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,320
You don't understand.

668
00:29:36,410 --> 00:29:38,230
It's the new fashion.

669
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:40,280
I really don't get your fashion.

670
00:29:41,700 --> 00:29:42,800
Li Qing Tong!

671
00:29:43,790 --> 00:29:45,010
I'm coming.

672
00:29:50,460 --> 00:29:51,520
Do you miss me?

673
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:56,050
You...

674
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,050
Did you get hit in your eyes?

675
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:00,060
Cut the crap, Stupid Egg.

676
00:30:00,150 --> 00:30:01,080
Who are you calling stupid?

677
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:02,230
Call me Mr Egg.

678
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,510
You should call me
your elder sister first.

679
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:04,240
Hurry up.

680
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:06,370
You're only one week older than me.
Honestly!

681
00:30:06,490 --> 00:30:08,640
I'm your elder sister even if
I'm one day older than you.

682
00:30:11,500 --> 00:30:12,580
A new face.

683
00:30:12,890 --> 00:30:14,160
Aren't you introducing us?

684
00:30:15,170 --> 00:30:16,320
This is Hua.

685
00:30:16,530 --> 00:30:17,400
She's from Shenzhen.

686
00:30:17,490 --> 00:30:18,590
She's my childhood friend.

687
00:30:19,230 --> 00:30:19,990
Hello.

688
00:30:20,070 --> 00:30:20,940
My real name is Wang Xiao Min.

689
00:30:21,090 --> 00:30:22,120
You can call me Egg.

690
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:23,870
Your last name is Wang?

691
00:30:24,650 --> 00:30:25,670
And first name is Egg?

692
00:30:28,940 --> 00:30:29,820
Good name.

693
00:30:30,130 --> 00:30:31,010
You don't understand.

694
00:30:35,660 --> 00:30:36,810
Xiao, why are you here?

695
00:30:36,890 --> 00:30:38,160
Didn't you say you won't come?

696
00:30:38,250 --> 00:30:39,760
When did I say I won't come?

697
00:30:39,850 --> 00:30:40,730
My goodness.

698
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,020
Goodness gracious.

699
00:30:42,450 --> 00:30:44,000
Let's go to dinner.

700
00:30:44,090 --> 00:30:45,120
Hurry up.

701
00:30:45,210 --> 00:30:46,160
Let's go.

702
00:30:48,090 --> 00:30:49,310
How fat you are!

703
00:30:51,740 --> 00:30:53,280
Well, let me say something.

704
00:30:53,430 --> 00:30:55,690
Today, we're welcoming a new millennium.

705
00:30:55,810 --> 00:30:57,040
It's commemorative.

706
00:30:57,140 --> 00:30:58,130
So, I decided

707
00:30:58,220 --> 00:30:59,330
to treat everyone.

708
00:30:59,420 --> 00:31:00,700
Help yourselves.

709
00:31:00,780 --> 00:31:01,660
Order what you like.

710
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:04,620
This is what you're treating us?

711
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:06,930
Why not invite us to
a high end restaurant?

712
00:31:07,300 --> 00:31:08,880
You're all my friends.

713
00:31:08,970 --> 00:31:10,280
This place is good.

714
00:31:10,370 --> 00:31:11,250
Try it.

715
00:31:12,190 --> 00:31:13,690
Isn't it hot to wear so much?

716
00:31:14,730 --> 00:31:15,610
But it's good-looking.

717
00:31:16,820 --> 00:31:18,920
I didn't see clearly in the dark.

718
00:31:19,350 --> 00:31:21,890
What have you done to your make-up?

719
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:23,940
You don't understand.

720
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:25,130
We spent the whole day
putting it on.

721
00:31:25,210 --> 00:31:26,190
Yes.

722
00:31:28,660 --> 00:31:29,590
Xiao.

723
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,690
I prepared a gift for you.

724
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:34,400
An American pen.

725
00:31:34,490 --> 00:31:35,440
My aunt brought it to me.

726
00:31:35,530 --> 00:31:36,320
Now, it's yours.

727
00:31:36,410 --> 00:31:37,240
No.

728
00:31:37,330 --> 00:31:38,630
It's too expensive.

729
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:39,680
It's not expensive at all.

730
00:31:39,770 --> 00:31:40,940
Only five dollars.

731
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:42,330
Even so.

732
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:44,400
It's okay.

733
00:31:44,490 --> 00:31:46,830
You have a gift for me anyway, right?

734
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:48,010
What?

735
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:49,710
When did I say that?

736
00:31:54,810 --> 00:31:55,760
The gift that he mentioned that day

737
00:31:55,850 --> 00:31:57,990
was not for you.

738
00:32:01,540 --> 00:32:02,600
Never mind.

739
00:32:03,860 --> 00:32:04,600
Don't be angry.

740
00:32:04,690 --> 00:32:05,870
Xiao doesn't want it but I do.

741
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:07,630
Have you ever studied?

742
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:09,030
What do you want a pen for?

743
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,050
The dumplings are coming.

744
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:14,700
The dumplings.

745
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:17,400
It smells so good!
Help yourselves.

746
00:32:17,490 --> 00:32:18,370
Wait a minute.

747
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:20,980
It's the millennium.

748
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:22,180
It's time to ring in the New Year.

749
00:32:22,270 --> 00:32:24,010
We should make a wish for the new year.

750
00:32:24,710 --> 00:32:25,580
Don't be ranked at the bottom.

751
00:32:25,670 --> 00:32:27,130
School break forever.

752
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,630
The school is buried in heavy snow.

753
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:30,680
Roll in the snow with a mink every day.

754
00:32:33,730 --> 00:32:35,010
I must win the championship of

755
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:38,230
the school basketball league next year.

756
00:32:38,470 --> 00:32:39,240
Don't bother asking Xiao.

757
00:32:39,330 --> 00:32:40,210
He has the same wish.

758
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:41,780
No.

759
00:32:41,870 --> 00:32:43,490
I have a new wish now.

760
00:32:44,800 --> 00:32:45,740
What?

761
00:32:47,330 --> 00:32:50,290
I hope we can spend the
New Year's Eve together next year.

762
00:32:51,630 --> 00:32:53,000
What about you, Hua?

763
00:32:53,090 --> 00:32:54,190
What's your wish?

764
00:32:55,870 --> 00:32:57,290
I have no wish.

765
00:33:02,410 --> 00:33:03,440
Well.

766
00:33:03,530 --> 00:33:05,040
I wish you all the best next year.

767
00:33:05,250 --> 00:33:06,040
Come on.

768
00:33:06,130 --> 00:33:07,250
Happy New Year, cheers!

769
00:33:07,340 --> 00:33:08,520
-Let's greet the new millennium.
-Right.

770
00:33:08,610 --> 00:33:11,270
Happy New Year!

771
00:33:28,250 --> 00:33:31,350
Sugar-coated haws.

772
00:33:31,770 --> 00:33:34,790
Sugar-coated haws.

773
00:33:34,970 --> 00:33:37,170
Delicious sugar-coated haws.

774
00:33:37,250 --> 00:33:38,200
I want to eat sugar-coated haws.

775
00:33:38,290 --> 00:33:39,840
-So do I.
-Buy it. My treat!

776
00:33:39,930 --> 00:33:41,290
-Come on.
-Buy it. My treat!

777
00:33:41,690 --> 00:33:42,620
Let's go.

778
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:46,140
Sugar-coated haws.

779
00:33:46,230 --> 00:33:47,110
Mister.

780
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:48,640
Wait a minute.

781
00:33:48,730 --> 00:33:49,790
You want to buy sugar-coated haws?

782
00:33:50,770 --> 00:33:52,410
Let me see.

783
00:33:52,670 --> 00:33:53,600
One for each, please.

784
00:33:53,690 --> 00:33:54,520
Okay, choose it yourself.

785
00:33:54,610 --> 00:33:55,770
You are too shameless.

786
00:33:55,860 --> 00:33:57,440
You buy so much
when Duan Xiao pays for it.

787
00:33:57,530 --> 00:33:59,050
What do you know? I'm growing.

788
00:33:59,130 --> 00:33:59,680
Back off.

789
00:33:59,770 --> 00:34:00,960
It's okay, help yourselves.

790
00:34:01,050 --> 00:34:03,310
If he wants,
buying him one of each is fine.

791
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,200
You're so generous.

792
00:34:04,290 --> 00:34:05,910
Okay, take it yourself.

793
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:07,160
Buy one

794
00:34:07,250 --> 00:34:08,469
get one lucky bag free.

795
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:10,739
A new year wish for each of you.

796
00:34:10,900 --> 00:34:12,100
Take one yourself.

797
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:15,580
Thank you.

798
00:34:16,909 --> 00:34:18,130
There's something

799
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:20,150
in every lucky bag.

800
00:34:20,580 --> 00:34:21,570
You can take it home

801
00:34:21,659 --> 00:34:22,840
and open it.

802
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:24,380
It won't work

803
00:34:24,469 --> 00:34:26,080
if others see yours.

804
00:34:29,489 --> 00:34:30,850
-Then give me one.
-No.

805
00:34:30,929 --> 00:34:32,239
Give me one more.

806
00:34:32,330 --> 00:34:33,520
You can't eat so much.

807
00:34:33,610 --> 00:34:34,239
I can do it.

808
00:34:34,330 --> 00:34:36,070
Don't worry, I can finish it up.

809
00:34:37,330 --> 00:34:40,190
Sugar-coated haws.

810
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:43,310
What kind of lucky bag is this?

811
00:34:44,650 --> 00:34:46,190
Let's see what's in it.

812
00:34:51,290 --> 00:34:53,590
"Study hard and make progress every day."

813
00:34:55,530 --> 00:34:57,020
What's this?

814
00:34:58,540 --> 00:34:59,810
Don't you think

815
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:02,270
the uncle who sold sugar-coated haws
was a bit strange?

816
00:35:02,580 --> 00:35:03,450
Strange?

817
00:35:03,570 --> 00:35:05,430
He looked nice.

818
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,800
His voice seemed

819
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:09,510
familiar to me.

820
00:35:10,450 --> 00:35:12,070
What's on your note?

821
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:19,600
You can take it home

822
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:20,980
and open it.

823
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:22,440
It won't work

824
00:35:22,580 --> 00:35:23,920
if others see yours.

825
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:31,760
I can't see it?

826
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:36,630
Think carefully, Li Jin Bu.
What can you do?

827
00:35:36,630 --> 00:35:39,320
[Think carefully, Lin Jin Bu.
What can you do?]

828
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:42,030
[What can I do?]

829
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,670
[If I can change Li Qing Tong]

830
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:46,180
[and make her better,]

831
00:35:46,270 --> 00:35:48,960
[will that improve our future?]

832
00:35:50,700 --> 00:35:51,920
[Li Qing Tong.]

833
00:35:52,220 --> 00:35:54,610
[The day has finally come.]

834
00:35:57,290 --> 00:35:59,030
So annoying.

835
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:01,020
I don't want to study any more.

836
00:36:04,290 --> 00:36:05,190
Li Qing Tong.

837
00:36:05,900 --> 00:36:08,050
Do you need someone to supervise you?

838
00:36:14,850 --> 00:36:15,900
What are you having trouble with?

839
00:36:16,100 --> 00:36:17,000
I'll teach you.

840
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:25,970
What's wrong with the two girls?

841
00:36:26,150 --> 00:36:28,130
Why aren't they up yet?

842
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:30,020
They're awake.

843
00:36:30,170 --> 00:36:31,270
They're doing homework.

844
00:36:33,910 --> 00:36:34,810
What?

845
00:36:43,620 --> 00:36:45,100
Then we have to keep our voices down.

846
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:46,940
Can you turn off the TV?

847
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:48,730
Don't disturb them.

848
00:36:48,810 --> 00:36:50,470
There is no sound.

849
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:51,830
Disturb them, how?

850
00:36:58,250 --> 00:36:59,670
Look at her!

851
00:37:00,850 --> 00:37:01,600
Shut up.

852
00:37:01,730 --> 00:37:03,510
Is it easy for your daughter to study?

853
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,480
My daughter

854
00:37:06,570 --> 00:37:08,270
is studying hard.

855
00:37:08,390 --> 00:37:09,340
She looks amazing.

856
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:15,710
Dad, I'm hungry.

857
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:16,700
She's hungry.

858
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:18,360
Eat after finishing the test paper.

859
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:22,990
Mum.

860
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:24,500
Hua is right.

861
00:37:24,580 --> 00:37:26,000
Eat after finishing the test paper.

862
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:28,720
Dad.

863
00:37:29,910 --> 00:37:31,220
Your mother is right.

864
00:37:31,380 --> 00:37:33,480
Eat after finishing the test paper.

865
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:45,220
What's wrong with you?

866
00:37:45,470 --> 00:37:46,890
Are you sick?

867
00:37:47,180 --> 00:37:48,090
Did you lose your mind?

868
00:37:48,220 --> 00:37:49,720
I can take you to the hospital.

869
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:55,140
[It's time to say it.]

870
00:37:55,690 --> 00:37:56,870
How dare you, Li Qing Tong!

871
00:37:56,960 --> 00:37:57,610
Who's insane?

872
00:37:57,690 --> 00:37:59,460
Are you proud of not studying hard?

873
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:00,870
[You used to scold me every day.]

874
00:38:00,970 --> 00:38:03,160
[Now it's my turn.]

875
00:38:03,290 --> 00:38:05,510
Do you have a fever?

876
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:06,480
Don't talk nonsense.

877
00:38:06,570 --> 00:38:07,450
Do your homework.

878
00:38:07,700 --> 00:38:08,450
I'm telling you.

879
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:09,200
As long as I stay here

880
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:10,390
I'll supervise your study.

881
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:11,930
I'll help you go to a good college.

882
00:38:12,020 --> 00:38:13,740
I'll make you a new Li Qing Tong.

883
00:38:13,830 --> 00:38:15,090
Understand?

884
00:38:17,090 --> 00:38:18,040
Hua.

885
00:38:18,190 --> 00:38:19,180
Why not think about

886
00:38:19,260 --> 00:38:20,340
going home now?

887
00:38:20,430 --> 00:38:21,220
I think...

888
00:38:21,350 --> 00:38:23,200
I think your mother is worried about you.

889
00:38:23,290 --> 00:38:24,140
No.

890
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:25,030
She is not worried.

891
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:26,550
My mother thinks the same as me.

892
00:38:27,510 --> 00:38:28,350
Finish the paper.

893
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,590
I will call auntie if you don't do it.

894
00:38:29,700 --> 00:38:31,530
-Auntie!
-I'll do it now.

895
00:38:45,630 --> 00:38:49,500
[Award, Outstanding Primary Student]

896
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,310
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

897
00:39:18,290 --> 00:39:19,750
Which class are you from?

898
00:39:21,720 --> 00:39:23,380
I made a mistake.

899
00:39:40,690 --> 00:39:45,140
[Learned, Inspired, Educated]

900
00:39:49,010 --> 00:39:49,890
Stop.

901
00:39:56,890 --> 00:39:57,860
What are you doing?

902
00:40:05,490 --> 00:40:06,870
Sir.

903
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:08,470
I am Year 2 student.

904
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:09,710
I forgot to bring my homework.

905
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,990
My teacher asked me to bring it here.

906
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:11,960
No.

907
00:40:13,030 --> 00:40:14,420
Go back and ask the teacher for a note.

908
00:40:30,500 --> 00:40:33,780
[Class on duty: Year 2 Class 3]

909
00:40:44,010 --> 00:40:45,390
Dude.

910
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:49,300
Do you like to speak ill
of people behind their backs?

911
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:54,390
Then why did you go
to the teacher and speak ill of me?

912
00:40:54,530 --> 00:40:56,390
And you spoke to the director.

913
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:59,940
Do you know you're being rude?

914
00:41:05,910 --> 00:41:07,370
[Boys' toilet]

915
00:41:07,370 --> 00:41:08,550
Chen Jun He.

916
00:41:08,810 --> 00:41:09,410
What's up?

917
00:41:09,490 --> 00:41:10,910
Want to play basketball tonight?

918
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,390
No.

919
00:41:13,330 --> 00:41:15,510
I'm teaching him a lesson.

920
00:41:16,180 --> 00:41:17,580
I'm asking you.

921
00:41:17,670 --> 00:41:19,280
Say something.

922
00:41:19,380 --> 00:41:21,240
[Chen Jun He?]

923
00:41:23,100 --> 00:41:23,810
What's his name?

924
00:41:23,890 --> 00:41:24,930
Chen Jun He.

925
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:27,940
He was our high school classmate.

926
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:28,840
Not anyone important.

927
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:29,390
[People's Republic of China
Divorce Certificate]

928
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,090
Is Chen Jun He my father?

929
00:41:31,170 --> 00:41:32,800
According to the divorce certificate,

930
00:41:32,890 --> 00:41:34,290
you divorced three months
after I was born.

931
00:41:34,380 --> 00:41:35,490
Why are you two divorced?

932
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:36,810
Did he cheat on you?

933
00:41:36,890 --> 00:41:38,360
He didn't care about me for 17 years.

934
00:41:38,450 --> 00:41:40,190
And he never appeared.

935
00:41:45,530 --> 00:41:47,510
[It's been 17 years.]

936
00:41:47,740 --> 00:41:49,280
[Finally, I meet you.]

937
00:42:04,370 --> 00:42:05,160
Jerk.

938
00:42:05,250 --> 00:42:06,510
Stand up!
